args: Draggy-draggy dragoooons! \nSo many different dragons!\nGonna meet me a draaaa-gon! ♪
Hee hee! I'm just in such a good mood,\nI just can't help belting out a tune.\nThis one is about dragons.
See, dragons in my world are all like\nlizards or crocodiles, and I really want\nto meet one that's different.
Yeah, it's pretty great how many different\ntypes of dragons we have around here.
Heck, Gaibhne and Creidhne actually look\nlike bunnies! They're SOOOO cute!
Always surprises me how you're the type'a\ndame what bumps gums about cute stuff.
Everyone loves cute things deep down.\nAnd if they don't, that just leaves more\nof them for ME to love!
I like a flapper what knows her onions—\nreally makes my socks roll!
You have bunny-dragons?\nI am VERY interested in this.\n...*drool*
Are we going to meet them today?
Nope. We're going to see Roc.\nShe's more like a bird.
A bird? Ooh! I'm feeling hungr—\nEr, I mean, I'm feeling excited!
Yeah, she's the real cat's meow, all right.\nJust wish she'd get up the moxie what to\nduel me already.
You know it! My goal in life is to send\n1,000 palookas packin' in a duel.
But I got too good at it, see, and now\nfolks bum-rush the exit what before I\ncan even wander in the front door.
Roc seems like a real hardcase, but I'll\nnever know for sure until she lets me\ngive her the business!
...Say, you seem like a pretty tough dame\nyourself. Whaddya say you and me go\nfor a round?!
It's gotta be all the way, though—and no\nhard feelings what if one of us ends up\ntakin' the big sleep when it's over.
Well, I won't say no if you're serious.
But if I die in battle, promise that you'll\nturn me into a yummy potluck dinner!
Hot potato, this dame's off her rocker!\nYou really want us to sink teeth into ya?!
Of course! If you take a life, you have to\nhonor it by consuming it afterward.
I've heard that sort of thing before,\nbut you're taking it to a whole new level.
Still, it's pretty impressive you're willing\nto go to such lengths to be responsible\nabout the stuff you put in your mouth.
Oh, I think you're making this out\nto be a bigger deal than it is.
No, I think Vanessa's aces on this one, toots.\nI finally get why you take such joy from\nthe ol' chow wagon.
Sorry, but the duel's off. I gotta learn all\nI can about ya, and I can't do that what\nif I wrap ya in your shroud.
That big buzzard ain't all I heard!
Whoa, that bird is HUGE! Is that Roc?!
Yachiyo and Vanessa?\nNot the best time to visit, I'm afraid. \nThis foe is tough!
Don't go it alone, bub—let us lend a hand!
Get ready to dance, pal! Blossom Flash!
Nicely done, Yachiyo. Now it's my turn!
And I'm going to finish it!
Time to slice and dice! Princess Strike!
Thanks for the help, everyone. I don't know\nwhere that fiend came from, but I really\nhad my hands full with it.
It had already taken out a number of\ndragons in the area around this lake.
So THAT'S why the water looks a bit\nmuddier than usual. I thought it was\njust my imagination.
Makes sense if the dragon what's in charge\nof the lake went off to meet his maker.
I'm sorry, but what does a muddy lake\nhave to do with dragons?
Oh, I suppose you wouldn't know.\nSee, in this world, dragons govern\nboth mana and nature.
So if a dragon dies, it has a profound—\nand often negative—effect on the area\nwhere it used to live.
If the dragon in charge of this lake\nhad been killed, this lake would probably\nhave dried up.
I had no idea dragons were so\nimportant to this world!
Worry not; eventually other capable\ndragons will come along and govern\nthe mana in this area once more.
The world has worked this way\nsince time immemorial.
Well, it's time for me to go. But perhaps\nwe can fight together again one day!
I guess we should head back to the castle.
Why so glum, chum? Ya met a dragon\nand everything, but a chicken could walk\non that lower lip'a yours.
It's just that dragons are so important to\nthis world...
Which means I can't eat them, even\nthough they seem like wild animals.
*sigh* That bird looked so tasty, too...
So all this business about wantin' to\nmeet a dragon was just so ya could\nthrow it into the ol' stew pot?!
Ha! I'd heard you were a big eater,\nand you do not disappoint.
Do you think maybe that dragon sheds\nits wings like a lizard does with its tail?\n*sigh*
